76561198054265533,Not Recommended,244850,32706437,Posted: 23 June,all,Xanthyn,"To establish my credentials, I've logged nearly 1,000 hours in Space Engineers, and I have made a workshop submission that hit weekly first place and received a 5 star rating. I consider myself to be a very knowledgeable player. Heck, I even put my current gaming rig together SPECIFICALLY so that I could play Space Engineers. I love the idea of this game, and have layed awake nights dreaming of what I could build next.That being said, I can't recommend this game in it's current state, and it breaks my heart to do so. Development has been two steps forward and one-and-a-half steps back for a long time. The devlopers are on a weekly release schedule that sounds great, but VERY frequently results in weeks of an unplayable product due to previously solved bugs that are re-introduced to the code. The development team has also knowingly introduced extremely unpopular game elements (such as scratchy glass), and even introducing multiple iterations of the same poor design choice while pages upon pages of protesting user comments stack up. Many core gameplay elements have been added by community members through scripting and modding i nthe Workshop, but Keen has a habit of alienating community contributers by breaking scripts/mods with undocumented changes.Keen CEO Marek Rosa has more or less stepped away from leadership on Space Engineers in order to spend his time on a general AI company, and the resulting lack of leadership has had a significant impact on the game I once loved. I am still hopeful that reviews like this one will serve as a wake up call to the developers, and that the game will eventually become stable, rich, and populated. At that time, I would be more that happy to delete this review and post a positive one. However, until we see a serious 180 on some of these persistent issues, I (and many others) will be taking a break from Space Engineers and keeping an eye on competing titles."
