,Not Recommended,244850,33538626,Posted: 14 July,all,Sir Wafflez,"I want to like this game, I really do, it's a really good time killer but often i find myself struggling to find things to do.Space engineers has excellent creative freedom, allowing you to build any ship/base you can think of, however it's strength is also it's greatest weakness in that once you build these ships there is a limited amount of things you can do with them, because of this singleplayer in particular becomes quite boring rather quickly.Creative mode is probably the best aspect of this game, however the problem of limited things to do is here too, as the already small addition of survival aspects and rescource collecting are removed entirely, leaving you with just ship building. The workshop community are fantastic builders though, hats off to them for the stuff they make.The game does support mods, and often servers will have several to add on to the vanilla rescources, again here the workshop community is great and I can't knock them at all.Speaking of community, multiplayer SHOULD be the redeeming factor for this game, but it falls short.There's no inscentive for friendly player interaction or trust outside of private servers; more often than not players will group with their mates and hide off in the far corners of the universe, never to be seen again. This is because the build time/destruction time ratio is so huge that players have no reason to trust anyone or pick anything resembling a fair fight (Which, in itself, is rare) which makes pvp scarce and one-sided, even on servers dedicated to it.Servers often struggle to meet the needs of a dozen players, which heavily contrasts the expansivness of the game worlds, making servers feel flimsy and empty.I imagine a game with huge player corperations duking it out for territory with frequent fleet battles, abit like EVE online but with voxel building, and i'll scream off the rooftops about this game if that ever comes to be.Until then I can't recommend this game. Unless of course you like building things; by all means get it then, it's good at that atleast."
