76561198098250102,Recommended,244850,28534294,"Posted: 22 December, 2016",all,Zarenityx,"So, to start off, you do need a decent pc to play this game. Remember, this game just went into beta phase. If you are turned off by the idea of bugs, continuous changes, and constant reworking of mechanics, by all means don't bother with this game until it is complete (which may be not for a while, as improvements and content are constantly being added).But if you like the idea of waking up midway into crashing into the side of a planet, tearing down nonessential systems to save just enough power to not die instantly on impact, scavenging what's left of the wreckage, and setting up a bunker on a hostile alien planet filled with burrowing spiders, and setting up a distress beacon in hopes that a passing cargo ship will pick you up, then this game is for you.If you aren't a fan of games in the middle of the optimization process that may have some lag issues, then don't bother with this game.But if you are a fan of jetpacking on top of an enemy atmospheric fighter, grinding down the cockpit, shooting the pilot in the face, then building the cockpit again and kamikaze ramming it into the bridge of an enemy carrier, then being picked up in the gunner's seat of a passing friendly gunship, then this game is for you.If you don't think you would want a game where piston physics sometimes break down when flying in multiplayer, don't buy this game.But if you want a game where you construct a mining ship, fend off the occasional pirate, and begin drilling for ice to fuel your hydrogen thrusters, to discover an abandoned mining facility inside the asteroid, which you slowly build up and repair and turn into your permanent, autonomously maintained home, and begin work on an interplanetary exploration vessel that would allow you to reach the planets in the distance, then this game is for you.If you don't like early access problems, frequent updates, bugs, lag, and glitches, leave this store page immediately.But if you want to crew the apollo 13 mission while being swarmed by tie-fighters or establish a mining outpost on an unexplored alien planet, or if you just want a game where the developers are fully invested in improvement and there are limitless options for creativity, then this is your game.All of the scenarios I have summarized in this review have all happened to me in game within perhaps a few months of playing. I did get this game on sale, but would have gladly paid double the regular price now that I see where this game is headed and what it can do.Best purchase I have made on steam, hands down."
