,Recommended,244850,31377166,Posted: 26 April,all,Reverend D,"You've played No Man's Sky and Elite Dangerous....this game is really nothing like them.Vanilla exploration is rather limited to locating resources or searching for derelict ships. Fighting is a secondary thought as MP is buggy and PVE offers no real challenge with the boring AI, BUT the game is still a total time sink.For folks who play Minecraft for BUILDING, or can spend days BUILDING crap with LEGOs, this game will bring you joy (and sorrow, and anger, then more joy again). It has a 'buggy' physics engine (Hail Clang!), but offers massive opportunity to just create. I've spent days (literally) building a ship just to turn around and say, ""hey, now that I think of it, I could do this, this, and this so much better"" and I'm suddenly off on a new project. Combine that level of OCD producing building with a great community (awesome modders whose content really brings a new level to the game), and you may have some friend and family issues in the near future. The Devs are attentive (contrary to what you may read here), and regularly communicate with players and modders alike.  BUT (there's another big but) I think the majority of us believe the game will never be 'complete' or fully realized. I'm not sure if this a limitation of the engine, or that this game is more a learning/testing thing for KEEN to use in other games. Either way, don't expect perfection...ever. Updates will break things that you may have been working on for countless hours, then they'll be back working again...or not. Flip a coin.Notice many of the bad reviewers...""I've spent over 2,400 hours in this game and I just can't take X anymore!""You spent over 100 full days playing a game.  Exactly how does that equal out to a bad enough experience you would give it a negative rating?  I can understand 50 hours.  ""I tried, I really did, but I couldn't handle it"", not 2400.  That's getting your money's worth and then some.Yes, like I said earlier, there are bugs.  Most are getting ironed out by the devs.  We know this because they talk to us.There is a steep learning curve.  This isn't a game you can just jump right in and know it all.The game requires a decent machine to run.  Don't think this is going to run on any ol' system....it ain't gonna.Don't expect anything beyond a sandbox for building spaceships and such.  That's what it is.So, in conclusion to my rambling wreck of a review, for me it has been worth every penny. If you are expecting a great exploration / fighting game, run away quickly. If you have anger issues, run a little faster. If you have a compulsion to build awe-inspiring spaceships block by block, don't mind spending hours figuring out how to make X work, and have the temperament to not kick a puppy when everything goes to hell, you may have found your game."
