76561198085047519,Not Recommended,244850,31655163,Posted: 9 May,all,Fayle,"The best game of this type (vehicular voxel nonsense) in terms of overall capability, until the bugs, lag, and slideshow fps remind you that you can't have nice things.You can make just about anything you can possibly think of in creative singleplayer like mechs, giant rovers, huge spaceships, cities and whatnot. Which sounds great until you actually try to drive the giant rover, move the mech or even LOOK at the giant spaceship. There are massive hitches for every tiny thing you do, and the fps reaches comically slow speeds when anything even remotely interesting happens, considering the game doesn't straight up crash.So eventually you settle for smaller things, then find it really boring since there's literally nothing to do besides looking for rocks or random drifting junk ships. So you go online.You stumble into a hellish land where if you don't watch your step, you'll trip and fall off the planet.-You get run over by parked cars-Walls will eat you unless the floor gets you first-Your rover will randomly explode with more force than a bomb-A small floating piece of metal will tear your ship in half-You can kill a man by running too close to him-That man's body will latch onto your ship and throw it into an asteroidSo in the end the game mechanics aren't the things that limit you, it's the implementation of the mechanics. The developers continually add more nonsense that nobody asked for like lens flares and new (worse) UI, and claim to be fixing bugs but are so incredibly disorganized that all it does is break more things, often completely unrelated to the original bug.I've held out hope for them since they did put in planets, which was amazing albiet unoptimized, but sure enough they go and put the exact same system into Medieval Engineers. All that tells me is that they got lucky and are just scrounging around for a quick buck. They've been putting more 'effort' into making both games more moddable, which speaks volumes on their stance towards development.The game fills a void no other game does, and with a lot of mods and LANing in a controlled environment, it can prove to be a good experience. So if you're willing to put in as much frustration as the amount fun you'll get out of it, then this game actually is better than a lot out there.(salted but cautiously optimistic that Keen will get their act together, not recommended until they do)[EDIT 6/4/2017]Keen added in mutli-threaded physics- something that should have been there from day 1, but better now than never. It actually made the sim speed WORSE in a private server, which is probably a personal problem, but the update came with gratuitous breaking of unrelated things so I hold my breath. A step in the right direction Keen but it's going to take a lot more steps."
