ng, addition of steam workshop, camera blocks, spherical gravity generators.. The list kept on going, and following it was a very distinct downfall in both FPS and latency performance through the game for everyone as it became an EXTREMELY common complaint on the forums and yet it fell unto deaf ears as Keen Software continued to essentially ""speedrun"" the development of the game, not giving a single care in the world for stability or FPS performance before next year in 2015..They also suddenly decided to announce that they were making ""Medieval Engineers"". A spinoff from Space Engineers while SE is in itself a spinoff of another abandoned game of theirs called Miner Wars 2081 that can be found here on Steam, go ahead and read the reviews of it here:http://store.steampowered.com/app/223430/Medieval Engineers was a game that many optimistically jumped into, seeing that it had potential but not much of anything else, having next to none of the buyers of that game actually do any research on the company they were buying it from and just like Miner Wars 2081, Medieval Engineers was unofficially abandoned with the only news regarding it these days are empty ""developer diaries"" where they sit and talk on how round the planets are for 45+ minutes instead of adding actual updates to the game itself. Review ratings for it is currently around 25%, can be seen and read here:http://store.steampowered.com/app/333950/-----------------------------------------So, everything put together into a TL;DR, this company has absolute zero care in the world for delivering people a polished product or even keeping promises for that matter and much rather jump from title to title, hoping and praying to the powers above that this routine of theirs won't be recognized before enough people have been ripped off buying their ""games"". Just today as of writing this review, I went ahead and downloaded a fresh install of the game to try it out. I jumped into a well populated MP server.. And wa