,Recommended,244850,9647172,"Posted: 27 March, 2014",all,Thomas Jefferson,"UPDATED 2/2015Several months have passed since I purchased Space Engineers. The name of the game is exactly that: the challenge of engineering in space, being able to procure resources on site, and use those resources to become more efficient and defend your creations. Although the game is still in alpha stages, the potential is huge! The developers release updates almost weekly, most of which include new features that change game play and introduce new challenges! I don't want to be cliché and compare it to Minecraft. It's more like LEGOS in space, but you have to survive by creating all of your block from scratch, and procuring resources to keep you alive!Building ships in creative mode shows the potential this game has for creation, especially if you can imagine several people building, mining, and fighting at once. Multi-player AND survival adds a whole new kind of engineering challenge. All weapons exist and work in game, and the use of factions allows for greater organization when playing on MP servers.Space exploration is now enabled, which allows you to travel more than 6 AU's from the center point of the map. 6 AU's is 6x the distance from Earth to the Sun, so it's practically unlimited! The addition of derelict ships and stations is great, especially when you're drifting through space with the default spawn ship and little resources. Cargo ships now shoot back when you approach them, and there is a ""super secret AI project"" in the works.If you've been on the fence about purchasing SE, I wouldn't procrastinate any longer. The more people there are testing and making suggestions to the game, the faster it'll be released in beta, and final forms. Besides, the game is well worth it as it is!Just remember, this game is in ALPHA, which is before BETA, and you will encounter some minor problems than an unfinished game has. I personally have joined the forums at Keen Software House and have been involved in suggested features and bug reports.Pros:- Creative/survival mode- Multiplayer- Ship weapons enabled- Procedural asteroid generation / limitless map- Awesome damage and repair effects- Huge potential- Very fast development/weekly update releasesCons:- It's alpha; if you can deal with the fact that things will change over time (so far for the better), then this isn't a problem for you!"
