76561198055130328,Not Recommended,244850,35086931,Posted: 20 September,all,ShadowWarrior,"It could be a very good game if you like designing stuff. You just get lots of toys ot play with some of which are armor, but others have lots of interesting functions like sensors, cameras, timers etc. There's even a block for writing your own programs. It's also nice that there's an OK physics system, so you can crash things and it's interesting. You can spend a very long time perfecting your mining and refining operations, transports, and fighting ships, which is very satisfying.The bad news is that the game is too buggy and clunky. A lot of the time while designing is wasted on trying to figure out how menus work, or finding out that you can't do something which you should be able to, so your designs can't work.  (eg for some ofjects the timer block doesn't have separate on and off option for something, only on / off, unnecessarily limiting what you can do.) Some of the simplest things like saving a design are also too clunky (esp in survival). More importantly you might start working on great designs with moving parts just to realise, all those are effectively too buggy to be useable. (rotors, pistons) Even worse, sometimes major updates cause existing designs to stop functioning by mistake (happened to me with merge blocks). This just ruins the fun.A minor issue is that there's not a lot to do with your designs. The AI is pretty bad and boring in terms of fighting so you can't make good use of some of your designs, and other than there's just mining and refining and moving from one place to another. You have  to set your own goals. This is not necessarily a big problem though as the design itself and pushing boundaries could be the goal like in KSP.Note: I have only played single player."
