76561197999179494,Recommended,244850,11569115,"Posted: 5 August, 2014",all,Chipmonkey,"When it comes to survival games, Space Engineers is very well done. I've spent more time than I like to admit on this game due to the fact that it allows for a challenging, but rewarding experience. As a space engineer, you are unable to perform too many tasks on your own, as your inventory is severely limited and welding/grinding/mining speeds are too slow for massive builds. While that may sound as a bad thing, it is quite the opposite! It forces you to build ships/contraptions to perform the tasks for you, which is an aspect of the game that I really enjoy. If you think you're mining too slow, build a bigger/more efficient ship! If it's taking hours to weld your base, create a ship that can hold more building components and weld faster.Overall, I highly recommend this game."
