76561197973109369,Recommended,244850,20245371,"Posted: 2 January, 2016",all,Phoenix,"I can't get enough of this game, I have over 2100 hours in game (over the course of 2 years), and it's still in alpha.Think Minecraft, in space, but more realistic. Oh, and there's weapons, and giant spiders!Pros:* Frequent updates. There's some update every single week. Yes, every 7 days.* Fully destructible planets, with no loading screens.* DX9* and DX11 support* Extensive modding support that grows nearly with each update* In-game scripting (puts Minecraft to shame here). If you know how to write code, or want to learn, you can do A LOT, all from inside the game itselfCons:* Sometimes updates break things, but it's an alpha, so I expect that. You should too if you get this now.* Multiplayer can be problematic. I haven't had too many issues, as I mostly play single player, but many people have reported desyncing and bullet-through-paper physics issues. The devs are rewriting the networking code to fix this, but it's still ongoing as of the time of this writing. They are nearing completion though, so expect improvements in the next several weeks.* Planets are only available in DX11. This isn't so bad though if you think where the game has come. Planets were never even considered back when I got the game, when it was advertised for DX9. They've now added a new feature that wasn't promised before, so they upped the reqs to match. I think it's a fair tradeoff. Everything else in the game is still fully supported in DX9, and will continue to be.I'm not only a player, but a modder as well. The modding API has grown considerably, and a lot is possible to customize (player skins, blocks, custom functionality). However there is some stuff that cannot be uploaded as a workshop mod (UI skins for example). They can be installed outside of the workshop though, if you know how."
