,Recommended,244850,9889536,"Posted: 21 April, 2014",all,Metalgearz,"Space engineers is perhaps the greatest sandbox game ever invented.As the name suggests, it's all about space, there are spacecraft to design, bases to build and asteroids to mine.The physics and spaceship building is incredibly well-done, newton's laws are well at play, for instance, ramming a ship will push it away, and will force your ship to move back aswell (or atleast the part of the ship that survived), by holding the movement keys in a spaceship, it will start building speed, and without thrusters put in the opposing direction (inertia dampeners), it's NEVER gonna stop moving, so you have to put trusters in all directions, should you want to move freely through the cosmos.In order to make your ship fly, you'll need power and trusters, and in order to make it turn, you need gyroscopes, wich are ALL affected by the mass of the ship.The building blocks given by the game allows you to make fantastic looking ships and new items are being added all the time.Bottom line: this game is great, if you like floating around in space and building stuff, buy it, as it is definitely worth your money."
