,Not Recommended,244850,32415353,Posted: 14 June,all,Astute,"Having given it much thought, I would equate Space Engineers to a flippant Greek God. Amazing, incredible, and outright astonishing in the things that it can accomplish, yet temperamental, spiteful, and ultimately ironic in the punishment it dispenses.First off, I love just about everything about this game. It's cool, slick, and polished in a lot of ways. If anything, everyone should take a peek at Space Engineer's tutorial section, that's the vertical slice of what Space Engineers can and should be. Every time I come back to Space Engineers, I'm immediately impressed with what they've improved, and how much better it handles. I have great respect for the developer and what they've been able to accomplish.However, Space Engineers has one particularly fatal flaw. You'll play for a good while, dozens of hours even, only to have the game ruin your experience with some bug that comes out of no where and destroys your progress in such a way you can't hope to recover. Even worse, there is basically no way to plan for these bugs. It's as if you spent hours baking a cake, only to drop it into a ditch in your kitchen that just magically appeared.Spend 30 hours building a really cool ship? Now it explodes off into several pieces at lightning speed each time you load, with no way to recover or even rebuild it.Scrape together a small rover to help you get around the planet with the bare minimum supplies you had? 15 seconds later it pops off the ground and flips over, destroying some of its essential components, with auto-save kicking in mid-flip.How about that lander you took 45 hours scraping together the supplies for? You put a finishing block on it, just to have it sink into ground and explode, destroying your only refinery. This repeats every time you reload.Like a Greek God, Space Engineers revels in your triumphs, patting you on the back when you do a good deed in its name. Well, right up until it gets jealous of all the fun you are having, and decides to curse with with the most ironic and painful kind of punishment that you had no idea was coming.This was my 6th attempt at playing Space Engineers. Every time I play, I burn a lot of time trying to get to the fun part(aka, finishing something), only to end up rage-quitting because my save is unrecoverable in some way. Final Verdict, pick it up if you want an amazing space experience, just be wary that its temporary, and will probably end with you rage-uninstalling the game."
