,Recommended,244850,11458131,"Posted: 28 July, 2014",all,AnotherMaple,"OK, first off let me say this: If there were a neutral option for this game, I would select it. Let's just get that out of the way now.Space Engineers: A game where, essentially, Minecraft meets asteroids. That's not a bad thing at all. It's actually a pretty awesome thing. The graphics are good, even on low, the ships you can make are AWESOME, and the multiplayer...well, I guess it depends on the server. Here's my big problem...the controls. In the trailer, it showed an engineer flawlessly flying, building, repairing, and moving. This was not my case. The way to rotate parts is very odd making the construction of the epic mothership I have formed in my mind much, much harder. Rotating yourself is a little easier, but still a little clunky (I'm not sure how to describe it.)When, after much deliberation, I made my ship, flying was FANTASTIC. The controls for flight are very simple to grasp, and make the game so much more enjoyable. The only relatively tough part of flying is the landing ""sequence."" Other than that, flying = fun as hell. The destruction of ships is very fun, too. I sometimes start up a new world for the sole purpose of breaking apart ships.If I had to score this game, I would probably give it a 7.5/10. The controls were the main drawback for me. If they were...smoothened (Again, not sure how to explain) then it would be much more fun. However, as of now, Space Engineers is a very average game in my opinion."
