,Recommended,244850,11008626,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Ankoran,"UPDATE (Jan 30, 2015): This game is my new favourite in the library. Everything, plus many more things are added after my purchase and developer is continuing to update it EVERY Thursday without miss. Procedural galaxy (or map, whatever it is) with no boundaries made this a true jewel. I wonder if programming an AI is possible with the in-game coding system :)UPDATE (July 18, 2014): YAY! Batteries!!.. Developer is carefully listening to community and creating the game that players desire. That guy (Marek Rosa) deserves a space ship!.. really... I mean it! :)ORIGINAL ENTRY (July 2, 2014): Think of this game as a Minecraft in space. But with more in depth simulation and lethality.You can build any kind of ship or vessel as you like. You can even give them some useful roles to help you in your harsh quest for survival. Make them mining vessels and they will crush those asteroids to bits, allowing you to get minerals and raw ores faster. Or if you have enough materials, build a ship with welders to help you build that massive capital ship faster! If you think your old ships need salvaging or scrapping, add grinders to it and it will become a ship dismantler!The game has many different startup scenarios both in survival and creative mode. Something for everyone. You can get confused by the UI or HUD at first, but it becomes familiar over time. Game lacks a proper tutorial or detailed help because it is still in development. But you can find vast amount of information from the community and wiki site. A little tip for begineers: If you start to play survival, try to find an uranium deposit ASAP. Everything is dependent on it!I'll give it 9/10 points overall and definitely suggest it to anyone that loves creativity based games. In my opinion, this price is acceptable for such game. (Let's be honest lads!)As far as I played, I never encountered any bugs. My gaming rig only slowed down while the resolution is set to 1920x1080 fullscreen. I don't know the reason, but playing the game in windowed mode solved that, and I'm playing in windowed mode since then. Not too much of a problem if you ask me...""If only there were batteries or battery blocks (that can be charged with electricity) that are reusable over and over!"""
