76561197965489502,Recommended,244850,10197290,"Posted: 22 May, 2014",all,(SFC) Captain Binarius,"Although i am writing this review while it is still in Early Access, which i usually do not do. After playing 22 hours of this game, i feel i can say that it has alot of potential.The company has my support, with the ability to churn out weekly updates, which are not only bug fixes but also include either core mechanics/upgrades to the system or other new additions which allow a much more desirable experience.With-in its current state you already have alot of freedom with the ability to play in a creative world where you can enjoy creating massive structures and trying out new ideas or survival mode where you must gather materials and construct your ships/stations/weapons and components. All of this with the ability of multiplayer on both modes.That brings me to another point, the fact they have added multiplayer so early on in development, means they can get a look at how it will run and optimize it from the ground up. Each new mechanic which is added will also be able to be integrated into a multiplayer world both in optimization and enjoyability. Doing this later on would cause alot more issues as say they developed a mechanic into the system then added multiplayer and found that mechanic is not compatible with the way it runs into a multiplayer server, they would have to re-write the whole mechanic from ground up. Doing it this way means they can be more productive and work out the bugs early on.  Kudos to you.I definantly reccomend buying this game and supporting the developers, there is also a wonderful modding community already! Check it out and i hope to see you on an asteroid somewhere!"
