76561198032376277,Recommended,244850,29594639,Posted: 30 January,all,Hobo In A Suit,"Post in two parts: Message to KSH/Marek, and a review/endorsement./// @ the Devs, Marek, KSH ///Hi Keen Software House!I LOVE YOU GUYS for making this game. However, I know how tired most of you devs must be by now, working on this title for so long. I know from experience as a mixed creative and technical guy the fatigue from working on a project for so long. Just know that you have a huge following, eventhough a majority of this following does not log in every day, or even every week. Look at the bump in players you had when planets were introduced; amazing!In any case; remember we are all rooting for you in creating this awesome survival/sandbox/scripted campaign multiplayer-driven game. (Yes, Marek; Multiplayer is focal here for the majority of us. Multiplayer is not just a feature! It's 2017 :P)/// Review & Endorsement ///I have thousands of hours into Minecraft, yet I always disliked that everything was stuck to a grid. In this game, there's dynamic voxel terrain, and there's grids of blocks. Separate, physical, grids of blocks. Blocks with their own physical behaviours too, such as rotors, thrusters, wheels with suspensions, pistons, connectors (connect grids). There's 'crafting', there's a survival mode that honestly does still need fleshing out, and most importantly there is the cluster♥♥♥♥ of blocks that you can put together in an infinite amount of ways that'll create anything you set your mind to creating; from orbital bombers to scripted guided missiles, defender drones, mining ships, racing ships, friggin' lunar buggies, carrier ships, ALL THE SHIPS, and even stuff like tabletop games and♥♥♥♥♥♥And next to all that you have a new scenario-maker that is the best 'build your own game'-game with ever better control over ever better AI. Yes, yes, and more yes. The potential is great, and as of right now is already much fun, if not for the buggy multiplayer and occasional physics screw-up."
