,Recommended,244850,7870678,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,FacelessCog,"If you enjoyed Minecraft and you're a fan of sci-fi, this is your chance to get in on the ground floor of something awesome.  If you were around in the beginning of Minecraft, you know that those who purchased the game early on, during the alpha, were rewarded by getting it at a cheaper price than it would eventually and the chance to enjoy it from the get-go.Well, meet Space Engineers.  People have called it ""Minecraft in Space""...and they wouldn't necessarily be wrong, but that also doesn't fully describe what's going on here.  Sure, it's a voxel based sandbox in space, but the cubes that are pretty much your only option when it comes to construction in Minecraft are just one of many building blocks in Space Engineers.  Half blocks, corner blocks, window grates, pillars, armor plating, etc...these are just some of the construction blocks.  But, on top of all that, you must then consider adding power, propulsion, lighting, tools, gravity generators, gyros and anything else you think your craft or station might need.Even though it is still quite early in Alpha, you can already tell that this game is going to be something special.  If you even think that you might like something like this, you'd be missing something special if you didn't get in on this game."
