76561198040011137,Not Recommended,244850,25759981,"Posted: 28 September, 2016",all,The Greginald,"There's a lot of potential in this game. Just a quick peek at the workshop is enough to convince some people to buy this game, and Ive sunk many hours into the game experimenting with highly customized ships and diverse mods.Despite that, there are some things holding this game back that really detracted from my enjoyment and resulted in my recommendation to avoid this game.Mainly, poor optimization. Ive played single player and made numerous ships and stations, and each save game gets increasingly unplayable as I go. Framerate drops occur within an hour of playing and continue to decline. I can only put a dozen hours into a world before I'm forced to start over, unless constantly destroy old stuff as I go. And if you use mods, the same problems occur, at a much greater rate.Long-term goals and achivements haven't really been implemented, so there isn't much reason to play survival aside from increasing the time and difficulty it takes to build anything.The game has also been in EA for three years and I'm unsure how well development will continue. I do think it's worthwhile keeping an eye on this, however."
