,Recommended,244850,11737432,"Posted: 16 August, 2014",all,NUCLEAR SNAKE,"Date posted: 16th Aug 2014TL:DR; Game engine and mechnics are finished, just needs more content. High Recommendation.For early access this is one of the most stable and polished early access games around. While the price is quite high it is clera the developers are constantly working on this game with updates every few weeks.Graphics are quite good for such a game and performance is fairly good considering what is being modelled. Super large ships will grind the game to a halt and it would be nice for some macro-based optimisations.Content is short, few colours, few block types (still a lot but not enough when compared to say minecraft).Gameplay has minor issues but nothing that ruins the gameplay. Game locks for a half second when saving and there is currently no way to brace for meteor impact. Also Gravity mechanic needs to become spherical to allow orbits etc.Creative mode is a nice little playground and features like copy & paste make for some interesting scenarios.Survival mode is good, however more events need to occur and possibly some NPC enemies/neutral/allies. My recommendations for survival mode additions are:- Solar Flare (turns all blocks off for 20 seconds, requires manual restart of systems)- Large Asteroids that move (this allows for large asteroid to smash into each other and send rocks flying out)- System degradation (systems over a long period of time should degrade)- System failure (if a reactor is comprimised there should be a chance of the reactor going critical and blowing up)- Unknown Event (An event that cannot be identified, power going out, ship being thrown across space etc)"
76561197999220006,Recommended,244850,11720952,"Posted: 15 August, 2014",all,Silenvo,"I whole heartedly recommend this game for any and all who love to tinker, build, design, explore, and then crash and blow up their ships in conflict with one another. It hasn't even gotten out of alpha and its still one of the most impressive games I have yet to play. Reminds me a great deal at length of playing minecraft in its early years, if this game keeps going and advancing at the pace it has, we will see something that I can safely say can contend with that particular game in the future!Admittedly that was probably very fanboyish up there so I'll talk about whats good, whats bad, and where it is as of 8/15/2014.The Good: You can build to your hearts desire and design ships and stations and collide them into eachother or other things for endless amounts of fun. The multiplayer enables some very good options of creative entertainment and crazy antics with other players. I honestly can't wait for some more advanced survival options to be implimented in the near future.It updates fairly regularly, about once a week, sometimes more or less often at this time. often including new blocks or adjustments - or just bug fixes to various issues that arrise.It has a newly formed modding community that is rapidly growing and improving (from what I can tell) and lots of creative people producing interesting creations that stretch the limits of what the game already has to offer.The Bad: I have to say that, after all the good things, you may be wondering ""Whats bad about it!? This sounds awesome!"" But I have to say that - There are a number of issues. The game demands a lot of running capacity, crashes every so often, lags a lot when lots of smaller scale or several large scale collisions are happening (such as taking your giant ship you just made and crashing it into a space station.. or an asteroid.), lacks a strong direction in story or survival means, and so far only really has its biggest fill from creative construction. Not to mention that currently the mods available for the game are mostly random parts that are for aesthetics only rather then any fantastic new game-changing items.However, this is only an alpha. Assuming the makers of this game keep working on it well through that, beta, and eventually final release? I can see worlds of creative options and entertainment coming about by this particular game. It honestly feels like an all new and better version of minecraft thus far. Moving blocks that include diagnals, my God! I can scarcely contain my excitement for more updates! Thus concludes my review.-Silenvo,The Silver Dragon."
