,Recommended,244850,11547896,"Posted: 4 August, 2014",all,Shark4-6,"I really liked Minecraft and I am glad that one cannot see how many hours of my life I have logged into that game. So when I saw a review of this game I thought ""wow, that looks like Gary's Mod and Minecraft had a baby, and then flung that baby into space."" I really like the game though, because of the same ""rules"" that are applied in game. You try to survive in space, a very harsh and unforgiving environment, and mine different ores out of astroids to build your ship. Now this is only survival mode, which I have not played any of. My 50.1 hours of gameplay so far has been completely in the creative mode of the game, which allows the player to generate any of the ""blocks"" (I guess thats what I will call them). I have had a lot of fun designing and flying ships that I have built. Also, with the flying comes the physics engine, which is one of the best I have seen so far. The only trade off to a great physics engine is the occasional lag spike, during which the computer is calculating where all the bits of my ship have gone. Now, it is also like minecraft, in the sense that it can get monotonous. You do have to come up with projects to keep the game going. But this is only coming from my experience in the creative mode, survival mode may be much  more rewarding, and I am sorry to say that I just don't know. In conclusion, I love this game, I think that if you liked Minecraft, you will like this game as well, and when I say its like Minecraft in space, I mean it. Also, just a side note. The Dev for this game is a really good guy, and has been (so far...) continually pumping out new updates and listening to players from the forums. So in conclusion (again) get this game."
