,Recommended,244850,11862897,"Posted: 25 August, 2014",all,GreyRogue,"If you've ever played Minecraft back in the day, during pre-release, and wanted Notch/Jeb/Whoever to expand more on the Contraption Aspect (Red Stone, Pistons, levers and buttons) than the fantasy, you're in for a treat.Space Engineers is what you've been looking for, and more!Space Engineers (SE for short) isn't your everyday sandbox game. Its a sandbox game... IN SPACE! The two main features of this game, so far, are:Creative Mode: A free build mode with the only limitations being your computer, and your imagination!- In this mode blocks are placed instantly, no resources are required to power your creations, and death is no issue (in fact, it can be turned off)- One of the newer features for Creative is the Copy & Paste funciton (Ctrl-X for cut, Ctrl-C to duplicate, and Ctrl-V to paste from clipboard)Survival Mode: In this mode, you can die.-When building only a Framework of a block is placed, and its required for you to gather materials (Through mining, or salvaging other blocks with your grinder) to weld the block to completion.- The health system is divided into two parts: Your suits power, and your actual health. If you lose power while floating in space, whelp, you gon' die, slowly. Remember ""No one can hear you scream in space."" The other way you can die... well there's a thousand ways to die in space: Smash your face into an asteroid, Someone puts a drill to your face thinking its sweet sweet Uranium, your ship gets blown up, Random space debris decapitates you. The posibilities are endless.Some with the vanilla items in the game to use at your disposal are:-Armor blocks (Your basic building blocks, you get Heavy and Light)-Reactors: needs Uranium for Survival. Powers your creations-Thrusters: makes you go.-Gyros: makes you go the direction you want.-Gravity Generators: Holds you to the floor (Sperical Grav Gens were just added, so you can have a planet!)-Rotors: Makes things spin!-Pistons: Makes things go up and down!-Artificial Mass: Makes your things actually fall with the gravity.-Wheels! You're no limited to just space ships.-Drills, Grinders, Welders: Typical Mine, Salvage, Repair-Guns! You can have a hand held SMG, Gattling guns( and Automated Turrets), and dont forget ROCKETS! (also in automated turrets)-MUCH MORE!SE also features Steam Workshop. ""Big Whoop, All ill be able to do is download other peoples things.""Wrong. Not only can you download user created ships, you can download custom maps and asteroids.Last, and most importantly, MODS! You can download user created Mods. No going into files, no making backups, not hastle. Sub, and its all done for you!Now your thinking ""That sounds neat, but its still early access. Itll probably just go defunct.""NOPE! Keen has been doing an amazing job and are dedicated to this game.They have weekly updates every thursday. And not just your every day hot-fix bug be gone update.Every. Single. Week. They add in new features and or Blocks.Keen also listens to the communites suggestions for new content, whilst still keeping their vision of the game true.Let your imagination run rampant!"
