,Recommended,244850,9500512,"Posted: 16 March, 2014",all,TheCatOfWar,"MINECRAFT + SPACE + GUNS + GRAPHICS + CRASHING SPACESHIPS+ ROCKET LAUNCHERS + BUILDING SPACESHIPS + LOTS MORE = SPACE ENGINEERS = BUY IT NOAWThat's the basics for those who don't like lectures.It started as a Spaceship crashing sim, more or less, and I bought it because that sounded amazing. It was. Hell, it still is. But since it's alpha, it's updated around once a week. That meant it got better by the week, and at the time of typing this they'd just added survival (and multiplayer about a month prior), which essentially made Minecraft, but almost everything Minecraft did, Space Engineers did better.Building is block based, but you get slopes and corners so you can make circular ships if that's your thing. You can build large ships, small ships or stations, and the main difference is you can use different things for each type, and blocks are much smaller for small ships (but use less rescorces if you're playing survival). If you want to build a ship the size of the death star, so be it, but mind it would lag.Surviving and managing ships involves mining ores, with a small hand-drills or ones built in to ships. You put the ores into refineries to turn them into ingots, then put them into an assembler to craft something, be it building materials or automatic rifles. Make sure to mine lost of uranium to put into your reactors, otherwise you'll have no power for your life support or ship systems. You always have a jetpack, to make getting around space easier.If you're more destructive then you'd like to know that the game's damage engine is phenomenal. Blocks don't just disapear when hit with other ships or weapons. They crumple, twist, dent, float away realistically. If you like you can just play in creative mode, build a ship with a ton of rocket launchers and go on a PVP server to fight to the death.OK, the game is AMAZING, but the only con I can think of is the fact it's rather performance heavy, and will eat away at your graphics card. If your CPU's intel, you're gonna need a decent card unless you like playing it at 240p to get a good framerate.With AMD, an APU (A4, A6, A8, A10) should run it OK, otherwise you'll need a dedicated GPU.Verdict: BUY IT"
