,Recommended,244850,9182849,"Posted: 19 February, 2014",all,MajorLemming,"Legos in SpaceThis is my initial impression of Space Engineers. In the time I spent with it, I built a ""Space Bus"" and crashed several different vehicles. The best way to explain Space Engineers is that is operates like Legos in space. You build whatever your imagination fancies out of blocks and other bits. Building is easy and efficient and really only limited to your imagination. You can also color your creation and fly it about the randomly generated space world. For those who fancy construction it does this very well.Of course, the ying to constructions yang is destruction. And you can do this with anything you build. You can fly ships into other ships, space stations, or asteroids. This is equally as fun as building in Space Engineers.But, Space Engineers does something even better. The Space part. The physics model is absolutely amazing. Flying ships is not like in Wing Commander or Strike Suit Zero. Space flight is based on actual physics. Thrusters are used to steer and move your ship. Bigger ships require bigger thrusters. Thankfully, Space Engineers understands it is still a game and inertial dampeners are included with your space suit. It makes moving about in space infinitely more easy. Of course, you can swith this off and have some fun just reenacting the movie Gravity.I have not spent much time in multiplayer, which traditionally is not my cup of tea, but it seemed pretty good of what I tried of it.Definitely worth a go, even in its Early Release state."
