,Recommended,244850,9072630,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Mr. Meatcleaver,"People say that this game is just Minecraft in space, but In my opinion that couldn't be more wrong.What this game has over Minecraft is:1) - Physics. Placing gravity modules in a ship or station will anchor your feet to the surface marked as the floor, and objects can easily break and float into space because of zero gravity.2) - Procedural destruction. You can snap ships down the middle and it'll split like a banana. The damaged blocks bend and crack, and its great fun to build something just to ram something else into it.3) - Interiors. Want to build a huuuuge ship and walk around inside it, complete with working engine rooms, infirmaries, hangar bays, observation decks, mineral extraction centers, control modules, bridges and more? You can go right ahead and do that. No ship or station is too big to build.4) - Easy to learn, hard to master. You can make little fighters or big carriers fast and without problems, but making something that really stands out and is appealing both visually and effectively takes time and training.5) - Multiplayer and working guns. Want to have space fighter battles, guns blazing and parts that get hit breaking off and blowing up? You can do that.All in all, this is a great sandbox game, and it is being updated weekly. If you're a sucker for constructing things and then crashing them together, then this is a game for you."
