,Recommended,244850,12443156,"Posted: 10 October, 2014",all,bubu,"This game hits the spot for those who want a more advanced minecraft-in-space experience. The price is well worth it and the co-op mode puts the icing on the cake. Working with friends gives you the feeling of a space community building an empire.You must work for your materials through mining, refining the ore, and build components from blueprints. Then, similar to minecraft, you begin construction. There is a lot of room for expansion and automation via turning the mining process from a hand drill spacewalk into a mining ship with a large drill(s) that you can put a docking port on to directly dump resources into your refinery. Don't like mining? Want to be a space pirate? Raid passing ships either by blowing them up and taking their loot or better yet, sneak onto their ship with your machine gun and take the vessel as your own. Strip it for parts, put it into the recycling grinder, or use it as is for your next raid.Space stations, cars/rovers, mechs, mining vessels, any size ship you can imagine from little fighters to battlestar galactica sized behemoths are currently able to be built in any shape or form you want. There are various map configurations that change asteroid density and the size of the map which can be set to unlimited.One of the only cons I have found is that damage taken (from running into things, or being shot at ) seems to be disproportionately high. At times you will bump into something at slowish speeds and the colliding components will break off. You can also use your hand held machine gun to blow a hole in the large steel armor blocks with about 40 bullets. These problems require you to regularly check up on your ship with a welder and repair damage.This game is a lot of fun!"
