,Recommended,244850,11337948,"Posted: 20 July, 2014",all,Anarki3x6,"Today's the 45th Anniversary of the Apollo 11 Moon Landing so I figured a review of my favorite Space Legos game is in order!At the time of this review Space Engineers is still in Early Access but it's already provided a ton of hours of enjoyment and zero g tomfoolery. There's the standard creative mode which is pretty self explanatory then there's the survival mode which adds the challenge and realism we all love.The hardest part I've found players having when adjusting to the game is the initial loss of direction after getting thrown into space. Gravity Generators are your best friend when starting off, especially when mining with the hand drill and exploring your first asteroid. After that, it's all fun and building. Right now there isn't much in the way of enemy NPCs (besides the occasional cargo ships you can enable) but I'm sure that'll be impoved upon in the future.If you're a fan of MineCraft that would like some more sci-fi complexity in their life, do give SE a whirl."
