,Recommended,244850,12631364,"Posted: 25 October, 2014",all,El Lindo,"UPDATED (November, 2015): NOW WITH PLANETS! Space Engineers is by far one of my favorite games on Steam. It is a semi-realistic game about building and settling in space, when I say half realistic, I mean that it also includes objects that do not exist in today’s day in age, some of these include; Artificial Mass, Gravity Generators, and Gyro spheres (keeps ships from spinning continuously). You can create anything in Space Engineers; and when I say anything, I mean you can build anything from typical space ships, to sprawling stationed settlements. Space Engineers includes a wide variety of items to use in-game and also has the ability to open your own server (private or online) to play with friends, so you’re sure to not get bored for quite a while. But if you do, Space Engineers works with the Steam Workshop, which means you can download virtually anything you want and use it directly in your game. One cool aspect of the Steam workshop is the ability to add different types of skyboxes. Skyboxes are basically what you see around you in space, but you can find many different varieties of them, from orbiting a strange gas giant, to being in the outer atmosphere of Earth itself. The possibilities are endless for this game, and the developers are very committed to it as well, as they continuously add many new items and fix anything that needs some tweaking. Space Engineers is an extremely successful game; Keen Software House has already signed a deal with Microsoft, stating that a Space Engineers is also in the works for the Xbox One platform. As for bugs, these are fixed very fast; therefore having to worry about bugs in this game is not a typical problem, I have never had a technical issue with this game or any issue at all. This game is well-worth $24.99 as it is very well made and receives the support and updates it deserves on a regular basis. The only con about playing Space Engineers is its lack of story/objectives, which means without friends playing with you, you may become bored faster than most. I recommend this game to all of my Steam friends and all that have purchased it have not been disappointed.My Rating for Space Engineers is (9 / 10)."
