,Recommended,244850,13742227,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,Quit Stalin,"My review goes through the Cons first then the Pros because I like to go through the bad stuff first than get to the stuff that Makes it amazing However I will have a quick summary Just below this if you don't want to read the entire review however you will miss out on quite a few things (Since summaries trade Information for Short and Quick Points.)QUICK SUMMARYSpace Engineers is a really fun game and it is quite Innovative it's also really great at what it does (Space exploration and Engineering of course) and has lots of potential I consider it a must buy, because the Creators are actively engaging and getting Idea's from the community, the Community in and of its self is the best I've seen for any gaming community to date however Space engineers does have some problems for example super large worlds can take up to 10 minutes to load, and Super large ship battles can literally drop your FPS rate to Unplayable levels (Doesn't matter if you have a super strong PC or not) and the game has quite a few Optimization issues however the creators are always optimizing something every update, and with every update they usually bring something new for us to play around with.CONS1. Controls- This game features the weirdest controls of any game I've played and I've played quite a few games with wacked out controls (The Metal Gear Solid franchise had some pretty wacked out controls compared to any game that was around during the games lifespan), So chances are you're going to be fustrated trying to figure out the controls thank god they put in a control changing menu in game however this still a load of controls you'll need to config, I've never seen a game with so many damn controls and all of them are quite useful thank god.2. Optimization issues- another con this game isn't really good at Optimizing full scale ship battles with AI weapons yet and that's because the game hasn't been fully Optimized for the AI weapons yet, However Player controlled cannons are fine usually atleast until tons of pieces start flying off the ships due to gunfire and what not thats when your computer will start to cry, even people with strong computers (Such as me I have a really powerful computer) will feel the impact on the CPU Processor. Large worlds can also really do a number on your computer slowing it down alot sometimes it can take up to 10 minutes to load.PROS1. Great Community- The community for this game is one of the most supportive, helpful and kindest I've seen for any game to date most will be willing to help you out with anything.2. The Developers actually listen- The Developers are always listening to the community and implementing things the community thinks are needed and fixing what bus the community finds that they haven't overall they're really active.3. Updated frequently- Frequently updated so when you do get bored and comeback to this game there's always something new to try out.All and all I could continue listing Pros but I just can't do it enough Justice if you have the money I highly recommend you try this game out."
