76561198069990894,Recommended,244850,10113746,"Posted: 14 May, 2014",all,ridleyeater,"Early access games are the biggest scam in the gaming industry today, due to being a quick cash grab for the developer, who can at any point abandon the project. Luckily, this early access game does not fall under this category. I bought this game a few months ago, and I haven't had a week go by without a major update to this game. The developer is clearly motivated to complete this game, and hasn't slowed down development in the least. Not only does this game have an excellent style (while not being very original with the style), but the game is also surprisingly heavily community based. I remember one line from the developer being ""You guys requested solar panels, so we added solar panels"". Not only did this happen in a very timely manner, they were also functional very soon after their release. Being able to make a community idea functional the way that these devs do, is pretty much unheard of in this industry.As for the game, it is very fun, but be ready to spend HOURS on end coming up with contraptions and other things.If you like physics based voxel sandboxes, this game is definitely for you. Those without imagination will find themselves getting bored quickly."
