,Recommended,244850,30783302,Posted: 27 March,all,SpicyWater,"Just such a quality, phenomenal game. This is quite literally, in my own opinion, the perfect hybrid between minecraft's prominant crafting, building, sandbox and exploration mechanics, and a physics game but in space with physics and ships that you can roam around in, and fly, and go from planet to planet in. You can construct space stations of whatever size and complexity you could dream. Additionally, there are so many different creative possibilities as to what kind of mechanisms you can build and the scope of the world you create is entirely up to you. This is an immaculate platform for realizing your imagination within a 3d environment and experiencing it through an avatar.I don't want to just ooze all positivity and perfection in regards to this game, but it has been a spectacular experience and continues to be - even in the midst of this era of games where we don't really see this level of developer passion (they've ACTUALLY been updating the game and bugfixing it frequently with a recently integrated story mode that clearly a lot of work went into) and this level of openness in terms of how you want to play it. You can go into creative sandbox mode, build ships with unlimited resources and fly them around and destroy them, or you can go into survival - balancing resources while coming up with crafty solutions to survival problems, or even go through and play the story mode. Multiplayer is EPIC and extremely satisfying.Now, to actually carry through with not just oozing positivity - the game has bugs. Not *quite* often, but if you are really testing the system (and i mean this in the sense where you aren't just playing but trying to break the system) then you will find bugs. They occur sometimes in very inconvenient spots, and I have unfortunately had my files go corrupt after crashes, but this is very preventable, and also highly unlikely, I just play alot and start new worlds often. I've had problems in the past with my PC running this (in terms of lagspikes/render quality etc.) but as of late it seems that the dev team really hopped onto not just the bugfixing, but also the optimization of the game. If you are looking for a game that runs as smooth as a glass surface then you may likely be disappointed in this, but what problems you may experience would not likely be game-breaking or mechanically altering. For having that pitfall though, the imaginative possibilities are absolutely astounding.I highly support this dev team for bringing a touch of honor back to the realm of beta/alpha testing. They let us play this game in it's early stages of development, we stuck around, and we as a community were continually rewarded for that. This game does not stop improving and this development team does not stop working hard for us - they're intentions are clearly begind this incredible game.If you're looking to play an open ended, imaginative sandbox game with endless possibilities, you ARE going to thoroughly enjoy yourself."
