,Recommended,244850,11202567,"Posted: 12 July, 2014",all,twitch.tv/AtlantisThief,"After playing around 110h, I decided to drop here a review for people interested in this game.GameplayThe current gameplay modes consist of ""Creative"" and ""Survival"". In Creative, you are given the chance to build everything you imagine without the need of mining/refining the materials, as well as you don't have to care about your health. The possibilities are endless, you can build basic small combat frigates or huge massive battleships.In Survival mode, your avatar is losing energy and must be refilled by either using a medical station or using a cockpit. You have to gather ore and refine them to materials. The later must then be combined to components using an assembler. You still can build everything you want, you must invest more time.At this point, if you like Minecraft and are also in love into Space this will be for you!GraphicThe graphics are okay, currently not over the top, but still good compared to some other games in this voxel-based games. The lightning and shadow looks good I couldn't find any FPS drops beside those looking at very complex and big structures (hardware based).MultiplayerBoth gamemodes ""Creative"" and ""Survival"" can be played in multiplayer, creating an online server for your friends is easy and userfriendly. In the current version (01.038) the netcode is still bad and causes some major issues on dedicated server, but it still allows you to enjoy the fun of cooperation with friends.ConclusionI am fully happy with my decision to buy the game and support the developer in the Alpha Stage. The game, as right now, gives me enough to learn and enjoy all my possibilities. My major game experience is based on multiplayer survival on a non-public server. With enough creativity and fascination of space and engineering, I can recommend the game to you.If you like my review, leave a message on my profile page and give me a ""thumb up"", so others will also have the chance of reading this. If you dislike something, please feel free to leave a comment on my profile page as well."
