,Recommended,244850,12499105,"Posted: 15 October, 2014",all,Jekht,"If Minecraft and Kerbal Space Program were to be mashed together, Space Engineers would be the result. Surprisingly polished for an alpha, and with a pretty vibrant mod scene.Positives:-Voxel environments that allow the creativity of Minecraft without the blockiness.-Frequently updated-Fantastic multiplayer-Great depth and complexity-Crashing stuff into other stuff then realising you hadn't saved-No need for local world wipes deleting all your hard earned progress (I'm looking at you Starbound)Negatives:-Pregenerated worlds are actually quite small (upto 16 big asteroids but it never really feels like you're exploring)-Survival mode still feeling a little feature light.-Lots of rubbish character animations.-Plenty of placeholder art, such as an awful skybox that only exists to hide how small the levels are.Despite all of the negative, this is an amazing game. I would have paid double the asking price if I had known how much I would enjoy it."
