76561198013758367,Recommended,244850,9151714,"Posted: 17 February, 2014",all,[W.I.S.P]Albrat,"I have logged a fair few hours in the game now and feel that a review is in order.Basically the game is in development, But the quality of development is triple A in my opinion.  Graphics are astoundingly good (very very very good).  The physics of the game, while not perfect, they do exist and maybe are a future improovement.The controls in the game, they take a little getting used too, but if you imagine the challenge of giving 360 by 360 control and not making the controls too hard... its been implemented very well.  I am still learning about features in the game and controls / methods of building!!.Building - The modular block building style of this space sim is excellent, as some have said ""minecraft in space"" but this is much more than just minecraft in space.  (though i think adding airlocks and life suppport systems to ships / bases would be a good future addition.)The multiplayer - This is at the time of this review (17-02-2014 *february*) a new addition to the game still, I think there are going to be improovements.The performance of the game...  I have no issues with running the game in single player, But if you wish to run a multiplayer game I suggest a powerfull computer at this time.  -- The reason i say this is that if someone crashes a ship at high speed currently.. the game will stall and calculate the damage and particles / parts that move away.  So multiple crashes or weapon damage will cause lag.Overall this game is well worth the price and I suggest that anyone who ever played Minecraft and enjoyed even a minute of it...  Pre - Purchase this game.  It is going to be a all time great!"
