,Recommended,244850,9782196,"Posted: 10 April, 2014",all,Skibby,"Did you like the movie gravity? Do you enjoy minecraft? And do you love sci (fi)? Than this game is for you.As of writing this game is still in Alpha status. But i'm impressed how stable it is, and how much can already be accomplished with such basic features.This game is about creating objects in space. From space stations, to small space fighters, and big motherships, or anything else you can think of. It has a creative (free build mode) and survival mode, where you need to stay alive, mine materials so you can craft new items, and repair/protect your creations from meteors and solar winds. The physics in this game is what really makes it stand out. Just by having a great physics system, and some simple objects like a rotor, thruster and drill, people are creating enormous self mining vessels.The game looks visually solid, clear art style and feel. For a game set in space, it's very down to earth with it's graphics, and still runs great on my 5 year old laptop (updated to windows8) and some lower settings. Untill the scenes (your creations) get too big, and the frame rates begin to drop. This will happen on any modern computer. Your creations can get bigger before you start noticing. But this downside is also it's biggest upside! They don't put any size restrictions, you can create what you want.The developers of this game Have a great way of developing this game, making them very flexiblle. And they really listen to the players, they actually prefer to build what we want to play. It's a symbiotic relationship that is working very well. Can't wait to see what the ""final"" product will be.10 out of 10 for an alpha game!If this would be the final game, it would still be an 8."
