,Recommended,244850,10336742,"Posted: 3 June, 2014",all,Cheridan,"A space sandbox and Early Access game done right.If you liked playing with Lego bricks as a kid, you will enjoy Space Engineers. Building a ship is simple, with each block you place changing the way it performs. A heavy ship will need more thrusters to speed up, a ship with more gyroscopes will turn faster at the cost of the high weight of the gyro. Too many thrusters and you'll need to add more power systems! It's easy enough to just slap components and make a lemon that will get you to the next asteroid, but players who want to optimize each aspect of their ship will enjoy the balancing act.The developers consistently deliver and impress with scheduled weekly updates every Thursday, each one generally adding a new gameplay element (wheels, gun turrets, conveyors) as well with bugfixes. I have complete faith that the game will continue to grow and improve, and I look forward to that greatly."
