,Recommended,244850,31083298,Posted: 11 April,all,Microsoft EXCELSIOR!,"I'm giving this a half-hearted thumbs up. The game itself is enjoyable my time in the game should tell you that much. It's just that the problems with this game are SO numerous.The connection in this game is horrible. I don't even play multiplayer I just connected with at one given time 3 of my friends and one of them could hardly play and kept spawning so far away he would spend 30 minutes arriving to where we were lagging all the way.It takes SO long to do anything. After the first 20 or so hours of gameplay, which was mostly just figuring it out and messing around, I actually started on a single save file. 95% of the rest of my time is building just ONE (albeit large) base. A good portion of that was welding literal hundreds of steel blocks. Another good portion was simply sitting in a mining ship collecting resources. You literally just press the up arrow so your ship keeps going into ore deposits found in asteroids. Depending on the storage space in your (mining) ship you can literally just keep pressing that one one button for 10 minutes or more and it is absolutely bloody boring. Then of course you to wait for it to go through a refinery.Balancing seems a little bit off in terms of resources. I've been on several maps that had absolutely NO uranium (power) within 30km. I actually went 5km away from base and used the host cheat menu to spawn an asteroid which luckily had it (it could have just as easily not). It did take about 5 minutes for the asteroid to spawn in but that's not bad considering what I was doing. On the plus side: You can spawn in asteroids. SO COOL!I don't mind other games where players can come around and just mess up you're base. But with Space Engineers you're not talking one or even three hours of hard work. You're talking twenty or more (and let's be honest since it takes so long you won't get anywhere just joining a different lobby any day). That is FAR too much. To the point I don't even bother with multiplayer only for someone whose been on the server longer to discover me and just ruin everything.Pros: But they're not just good they're GOODThe absolute NUMBER ONE thing about this game isn't so much as what it has to offer but what you do with it. How much you get out of this game is entirely dependant on what you put in. If you just play it Iguaranteeyou will have moments where you program a hatch on your large ship incorrectly and it tears itself off along with a hunk of your ship and hurtle off into deep space. Or experimenting with space torpedoes and honestly anything else where you're building, experimenting, failing, and going back to the drawing board. The appeal of Space Engineers is exactly that, it makes you feel like an engineer. And with the expansive scripting system in place you can build just about anything you want and if it so happens you can't it's virtually inescapable you can improvise if you try hard enough.So even with all the drawbacks I'm going to give this a 7/10 if playing alone. 8/10 if you're with friends. And a temporary 9/10 if you're doing something gloriously stupid. What you put into this game really defines what you get out of it."
