,Recommended,244850,9464046,"Posted: 14 March, 2014",all,Hex,"Amidst the mountains of debris and multiplayer ship ramming carnage emerges a new crafting and survival game. Space Engineers. The first few steps into this empty world will have you scratching at your head as you try to create a vessel to take you from point A to point B. A few hours later into this magnificent game and you will realise the sheer architectural potential this game offers. From tug ships to space stations to gravity propelled warhead launchers, Space Engineer's complex physics driven engine provides a space for every builder. Space Engineers offers players the casual ""creative"" mode in which you can build to your hearts content and the newly released ""survival"" mode.  Survival mode, as the name states, forces you to survive in the inhospitable stygian vacuum that is space. Mining for the ore required to build ship components, assembling pieces for your project and keeping your suits jetpack and life support systems charged are essential pracitces in order to ensure your survival in the new game mode. Although this game is still at a relatively early stage in its development it offers hours, days or even weeks of enjoyment for the casual builder or the hardcore survivalist. For only $14.99 this game pays for itself."
