76561198076254924,Recommended,244850,9936865,"Posted: 26 April, 2014",all,Wadayalookinat,"Ok, first off, I know that the game is still in alpha. A really good alpha though. I have some mixed opinions about it. I do think you should buy it if you have friends to play with. It is like a million times better with friends. It is very boring alone. You can always join a public server, so if you like playing with random strangers, the option is there. If you think a sandbox game in space would entertain you, keep reading.Gameplay: You choose if you want to play survival or creative, choose a setting and then you start playing. You can also choose your inventory size, turn on regenerating health, thruster damage, etc. You then start playing. There is no real goal in this game, but that is fine with me. ou can do pretty much anything at your own phase. First thing you notice is that the controlls take a while to get used to, but yo can change them, so its okay. Then you can build ships, mine minerals, shoot stuff, start wars, build space stations and whatewer. The ship building is quite simple. In creative, you can just place a block, nothing complicated, but in survival, you place a block, get certain parts you need to build it, then get your welder and you build the block. repeat 200 times and your ship is made. Grats. Ships can be used for a lot of things. I made a space bus, for example, and a mining ship. Speaking of mining, there are two options. With a hand drill or a ship drill. The hand drill is like the worst. Sure, you can dig cool cavesand all, but if you wanna just mine for minerals, you have to mine the ore, which is slow, and then you have to grab the floating ore. Unless you ahve a gravity generator on the asteroid. The ship drill is much better. It handles worse, it is faster and stores ores instantly however. Dont even try using the hand drill. Now the jetpack. You turn around with the mouse, you fly up with space (jump) and down with c (crouch). the jetpack can go like 100 meters per second, but it ahs really bad accelration. It is basically a ship strapped to your back, since it controlls exactly the same.Graphics: Graphics do not look that bad, I seen worse looking games, but this game is still in alpha, so there is no use in complaining. However, some texture are glitching up, turning to negative sometimes (Purple iron ROFL) and some are unfinished. But at least the characters and the basic blocks look nice. You can change colors of blocks, but not of your engineer. I am green, for example, but my friend is once blue, once yellow, etc. If you are not the admin of the server, you will change colors each time you join the game. So the graphics are alright. (DISCLAMER, THE GAME IS IN ALPHA STATE)Music: Turn it off. It's irritating and disturbes your voice chat.So, that's it for now. Here was my review of space engineers alpha. I would give it a 3.5/5 and not because of the graphics, but because of the gameplay purely. The game is unfinished, and I know there will be updates that will fix it, but for now, it will get that. (DO NOT TAKE MY REVIEW SERIOUSLY, ITS JUST MY OPINION)BONUS: I have found a weird bug, that if you run in caves or on stairs, you suddenly die for no reason. Please fix that."
