,Recommended,244850,14987627,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,Yung Cash Register,"Ok. First off I want to say that just because they made a new game called Medieval Engineers that doesn't mean they have ditched this game. This game still gets updated every Thursday and that is really nice to know how much the developers care about their game and their community.There are hundreds of tutorials on both, YouTube (mainly on the official YouTube channel) and in Steam Guides. These tutorials have never failed to help me either which I am greatly appreciative of.Also, the community is really nice! I have never had trouble with anyone, never met any trolls, never met people trying to kill everyone, never met unfair players, and never met bad sports! It's brilliant. There are also lots of groups you can join (mine is 121st Space Marines Unit) which occasionally collide into combat, fighting with lots of different roles and in different ships using perfect strategy in their epic battles to become victorious. I have never met a better community other than this one.Then there is the visuals. The visuals are beautiful! The way how you can be anywhere on this game and say, 'These visuals are amazing!' It's just perfection at the maximum. You can also download 'Skyboxes' which changes the background of the game. For example, a planet to look at (not go to though), a sun for light and stars big and small.The gameplay is smooth too. When you're flying around in a ship or a jetpack, you don't just jolt to a stop or anything like that. It's kind of like what it would be like controlling a ship in real life. When you're walking around, the bobbing up and down idea is fantastic. However sometimes when you're welding your hand decides to hover elsewhere other than the handle of the welder and lets you use telekinesis on it.Despite that, the sounds are also realistic. The refinery makes a very realistic sound as well as the ships and the jetpack has a VERY smooth sound. The music can either be calm and/or turn into epic music. The sound when you crash makes a big 'clunk' sound; the same with your drilling, grinding and welding too.To conclude I would say that this is an overall 10/10 game! I really enjoy playing it and talking to the helpful and kind community. And remember, they HAVEN'T DITCHED THEIR GAME FOR MEDIEVIL ENGINEERS!"
