,Recommended,244850,10156086,"Posted: 17 May, 2014",all,Mr. Dude,"It's easy to get lost in this game, in a good way. It provides everything an open-world sandbox needs which includes Crafting, resource gathering, survival and especially exploration which is where this game has so much potential in the long run. The default controls are somewhat easy to get used to, even though I sometimes found myself hitting the wrong button when two totally different functions are mapped so close together. Yet of course, this doesn't take away from the experience because its an easy problem to fix either by getting used to it or changing the mapped functions. Environments are limited as nothing but asteroids surround you, but because its currently in the Alpha stage, you can't really fault the dev's for it. Although, it would be really nice to get the chance to explore small life-sustaining planets in future updates. Crafting is simple enough to learn on your own without the help of the forums, although it can help you move along faster within the game. Survival is not as pressing as you might think. You may have a few pesky asteroids that can deal some pretty decent damage against your new ship or station. Except for when you want to explore, then, survival is a whole other story. If you're heading towards a Commercial Freighter and expecting an easy fight, think again, because they have some mean turrets that will rip you up, prepare accordingly. Yet even as it remains in early development, this game is so worth the price it's asking for. And with a community like steam to critique and help shape this game into something it's destined to be, I don't see how the Space Engineers team can fail. Being that this is my first ever review, I'm trying to keep both feet on the ground, but I want so much for this game to succeed, and then some. I think that when everything is said and done, Space Engineers will set out to get the job done for anyone looking for a new and fresh experience in the sandbox genre. The final verdict for Space Engineers is an 8 out of 10."
