,Recommended,244850,12448990,"Posted: 11 October, 2014",all,shandlanos,"Fun game, definitely doesn't have the polish of a full release, but well worth the $12 promotional price. I've only played solo so far, and aside from difficulty getting anything but the automated weapons to work, I've encountered few bugs. The physics system works very well. Even on solo survival the game is very easy, you can respawn infinitely and there's a short respawn time to get a new pre-built spacecraft - without which the game would frequently result in a dead end. There is no way to start absolutely from scratch - you need a refinery and a power source already in place to utilize resources. If you can't find a source of uranium for your reactor before you run out of fuel - you're at a dead end, and you must kill yourself to obtain a new ship with a freshly fueled reactor. Because each world is persistent, there really is no sting of death - you only lose whatever items you were carrying at the time, and you always respawn with the three basic tools to mine, weld, and grind up blocks for recyling.All in all I'd recommend it - it's fun as is, and has a lot of potential to be a great game as the devs keep adding new features. The devs seems very responsive to player input. I'm excited for the future of the game."
