,Recommended,244850,14679539,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,radj,"I'm going to start off by saying that this game is a lot of fun.Space Engineers has a very good physics system (for a game set in space) with the ability to completely disorient yourself just by spinning around in circles, whether is be with a jetpack, or a small fighter ship (with working guns), or a collosal frigate the size of a planet.Part of the physics system is the destruction engine, which is hands down the best I have ever had the pleasure of using. Ships (and even asteroids) deform and break when hit my missiles, rocks, asteroids, other ships, and even your face if you fly fast enough. To fix the deformed blocks you can use a hand welder, or, a welder attached to a ship! (You can also use this system to make a fully-automated factory for anything.)On to the suggestionsOne thing that space engineers needs SO BADLY is real artificial intelligence. Auto-turrets just dont cut it. Enemy and friendly AI would make everything better. Occasionally random ships fly around, and having actual AI just on board would add a whole new element of piracy to the game. (you can already hijack ships if you avoid their auto-turrets)Another thing is ladders, they used to be in the game but were removed, it would be great if they were added again, to use in elevators instead of just flying up and down them with your jetpack (Which can be very glitchy.)10/10 would smash face into wall again."
