76561198090743532,Recommended,244850,10006079,"Posted: 3 May, 2014",all,scoops,"If you like rescource gathering and/or building games that you need at least a minimal amount of planning to play effectively, then this game is for you.Alot of people are calling it 'minecraft in space'. I can see what they mean, but i disagree. I'd say its 60% lego, 20% Garry's Mod, 10% minecraft and 10% fresh ideas.In creative mode all building blocks are available and its basicly like building lego spaceships that you can fly around. Then in survival the blueprints for all blocks are available, but you need to collect the rescourses before you can place them. You can also play multiplayer games in creative and survival. You can set the options to allow anyone to join, or limit it to people from your friends list or even invitation only.There are 2 conditions I would suggest you apply for you to buy this game. They are that it is much more fun if you can find people to play with (its also one of the easiest games to join friends in that ive ever seen) and that you(or the person running the game) has a 64-bit system, as in a 32-bit system, there is a limit on the game size and if you go over it will randomly delete objects untill its below the limit. Happened when my friend was running the game and it deleted our ships.Overall, very impressed with what exists atm and still in alpha. You get to plan stuff, collect stuff, build stuff, fly stuff, in multiplayer fight stuff and if you really want (or if you are careless) crash stuff, which due to the physics system,  can be quite spectacular."
