,Recommended,244850,12320956,"Posted: 1 October, 2014",all,Flibedi-floob,"Excellent time-waster.You start off thinking you're going to build a ship, so that you can fly around and ""have fun"" somehow. (Of course you don't have any friends to have fun with, and should really be dating girls, but your lack of social skills is why you're sitting and wasting time playing games.)After stumbling around in survival mode, slowly piecing together stuff, you discover that this pace won't do, so you enter creative mode. You drag up a big, big field of building blocks. Yes, this is how big your ship is going to be, and it has room for everything: A bridge, and an engineering section, and maybe some crew quarters.So you start building, and you discover that you were wrong. This ship has to have a med bay too. ...and an armory. ...and hangar bays. ...and huge hangar doors operated by pistons. ...and maintenance ducts. ...and security checkpoints. ...and a cafeteria. ...and an officer's quarters. ...and an officer's mess. ...and a planning room. ...and hydrophonics. ...and a waiting hall. ...and a storage sector. ...and a refinery. ...and toilets. ...and a shower room. ...and escape pods. ...and drone control rooms. ...and landing platforms with blinking platform lights. ...and turret defenses. ...and interior turret defenses. ...and a brig. Gaaaaaah! It's good that space is so big, or else your ship wouldn't fit in it. You thought building a spaceship would take just a week of your time? Pfft. You'll be building your first ship forever. In the end it will be two miles long, and would need to have four layers of armour to withstand possible assaults from not only gunfire, but missiles, torpedoes and warheads that can otherwise just annihilate all you've built in no time at all.Now you just need to build the space station where this behemoth can dock....so in the end, this game is a lesson in humility. It contains everything you wanted for a space adventures except aliens. ...but I'm sure that this won't be a problem to implement either."
