,Recommended,244850,18338682,"Posted: 5 October, 2015",all,Darth Tater,"In a previous version of this review, that i posted Oct 2016, i said that you needed a supercomputer to run this game.This is no longer true.Now, you can run a game (without planets) on a potato such as a surface pro 3, at a mid resolution and minimum graphics at 25fps.A world with planets runs at 10 fps with lag spikes on a surface pro 3 at minimum settings.But this game is still incredible even without planets.Bugs are rare, but when they do occur they can often result in you dying if your nearby, and your fleet self detructing and flinging itself all over the place. This is a pain, but is not a problem if you disable autosave and remember to save regularly.The game also used to take forever to open and load saves, but now it appears to do these things much faster.Overall, I highly recommend this game (but maybe not if you have a really bad sense of spatial awareness, cos then it could pretty confusing)"
