,Not Recommended,244850,25175117,"Posted: 26 August, 2016",all,Ahrivaeus,"Awesome in concept, with a great building system and a superb physics engine. Regrettably, in the nearly three years this game has been available for early access, almost no progress has been made. Planets and AI have been added, as well as a couple of new construction modules. In short, don't pay $25 expecting a finished product any time soon.Additionally, the game acts as though it doesn't want to be played. Loading screens take an incredibly long time on a decently powerful computer. Sometimes the game will randomly pause, telling you to press the ""pause"" button to unpause it. This is not a keyboard button, and there are no clickable buttons in the escape menu which unpause the game either, which means you have just sat through the loading screen to exit back to the main menu and sit through another one.Survival is incredibly unbalanced, with many planets seeming to have little to no ore, and spawning packs of cyborg dogs up to six strong which can kill you in a couple of bites and take an immense amount of rounds to put down. Making progress in survival is slow, brutal, and often times simply impossible without setting the game to peaceful.All in all, 5/7, still better than No Man's Sky."
