76561197991010681,Recommended,244850,7906082,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,Zeorymer,"""The only way to get rid of a temptation is to yield to it."" - Oscar Wilde. That quote here can sum up the 'need', the 'want', the 'drive' to create something magnificent in Space Engineers.Space Engineers is an early release Alpha (which has limitations, IMPORTANT to note), that combines sandbox and creative elements and puts them in a Zero G, futuristic setting. While combat and weapons and a working multiplayer is in the works and not out yet, that's not the main attraction of this game at the moment. It's the ability to create almost ANY kind of small craft, large craft, OR station. It doesn't matter, the ONLY limit is your imagination. You can save your creations, and if you want, ram them into things to see real time collision and damage.If you're the kind of person who wants to test their imagination, patience, creativity, in an open sandbox game with more to come as time goes on, I HIGHLY recommend this game, hands down. I wish the best for this development team and hope this game has a bright future."
